ynos Tea I get 10 INT, 10 WIS, 5 STR/STA/AGI/DEX, 20 HP, 30 MANA.  When I equip Kaladim Constitutionals and Holy Cake I get 5 STA and 10 to all resists.  These stat modifications are essentially free and stack with everything.  The only cost is that you periodically have to force feed yourself cheap food and drink.  If you forget... well each of these foods last over 2 hours normally and sell for under 10p.  With Improved Metabolism, the food lasts even longer.  With a horse, much shorter time.  IM3 and the horse balance each other out.<br>
<br>
I see people offering thousands and thousands of plat for equipment that is only a few points over their current gear.  A Ring of Lightning sells for 50kpp on my server.  A Shadel Bandit Ring (1k) and a stack of picnics (125p) and tea (200p) has similar stats (more mana, less ac, more general stats, different saves). Not to mention the fact that by swapping out food you can change your stats for different situations.<br>
<br>
The best pure INT food for the money is probably Cheesy Vegetable Casserole.  People use it to skill up on, and since it doesn't have all of the stats of picnics, it often sells in the bazaar for 1-2pp.  It lasts two hours.<br>
<br>
Since illusion potions came out, cannibalistic food is harder to find in the bazaar.  Dark Elf, High Elf, and Gnome parts are all in high demand for potions.<br>
<br>
You might want to go to Cobalt Scar and ask the drake hunters for any meat they get (check the otter merchants too).  Pickled Drake is 2 INT, 2 WIS and is fairly easy to make.<br>
<br>
As for store bought, I wouldn't know.  That stuff all tastes stale to me.<br>
<br>
Quesci Jinete<br>
